---
import OldWebLayout from '@/layouts/OldWebLayout.astro';
---
<OldWebLayout title="DMCA (lol)" section="voidshell">
  <div class="status-strip">
    <span>void</span>
    <span>dmca</span>
    <span>not a real desk</span>
    <span><a href="/void">return to portal</a></span>
  </div>

  <h1>DMCA Notice Desk (Closed)</h1>

  <p class="tagline-block">
    There is no DMCA desk at VOID. The page is here for completeness. Most pages
    that look official are not. This one is not. Neither are the others.
  </p>

  <section class="old-shell">
    <div class="old-header">If you must</div>
    <div class="old-body">
      <p>
        VOID does not host the pages it links to. Pages live wherever pages live.
        The directory is a list. Lists do not own things.
      </p>
      <p>
        If a page violates your rights, contact the page. Most pages cannot be contacted.
        That is also a lie.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="old-shell">
    <div class="old-header">Real corporate channels</div>
    <div class="old-body">
      <p>
        Real legal correspondence intended for the operators of this site can go to
        the OmniShift counsel desk through the corporate side at <a href="/portal">/portal</a>.
        They will not read it either, but they will file it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <p class="memo-box">
    The bit can be weird. The boundary must be clear: if it's a real legal matter,
    contact the real operator. This page is bit.
  </p>
</OldWebLayout>
